This project uses [TASKS.md](https://github.com/tasksmd/tasks.md) for agent and human task tracking.

## Format

Tasks live under four priority headings:
```
## P0  — System broken or users blocked. Drop everything.
## P1  — Core work that should ship. Default for planned features.
## P2  — Valuable but not blocking. After P0 and P1 are clear.
## P3  — Someday. Kept for reference, not actively worked.
```

Each task is a Markdown checkbox:
```markdown
- [ ] Short imperative description
  - **ID**: auth-fix
  - **Tags**: backend, auth
  - **Details**: Implementation guidance and context
  - **Files**: `src/auth/refresh.ts`
  - **Acceptance**: Definition of done
  - **Blocked by**: other-task-id
```

## Rules

- **Completed tasks are removed**, never checked off. Git log is your history.
- **Sub-tasks** use nested `- [x]` checkboxes to track progress. Parent owns all sub-tasks.
- **Promote to separate tasks** when steps can be parallelized or span multiple sessions. Use `**Blocked by**:` for dependencies.
- **Claim tasks** by appending `(@your-name)` before starting work.
- **Add new tasks** you discover during implementation — use P2 if unsure of priority.

## Validation

```bash
npx @tasks-md/lint TASKS.md
```
